Notes:
Due to relativistic effects the L edge of Gd is ~ 8377 eV (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jqsrt.2019.106585). Galli used 8480 eV.
Due to approximations (such as removing the 5th shell) and without relativistic effects, the HF code underestimates it at 7417 eV.  
Thus to explore the effect we reduce the energy to match the L-edge to photon energy gap of 103 eV.


